headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 32 points, 12 rebounds and nine assists as the Philadelphia 76ers beat the Brooklyn Nets 121-99 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid, Maxey and Melton lead 76ers to a 121-99 win over Nets

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam scored 23 points, Scottie Barnes and Dennis Schroder each had 17 and the Toronto Raptors never trailed in beating Detroit 142-113 on Sunday, handing the struggling Pistons their 11th consecutive loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Raptors set franchise record with 44 assists, hand Detroit 11th straight loss

headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero scored 24 points, Franz Wagner added 19, and the visiting Orlando Magic routed the Indiana Pacers 128-116 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Banchero leads fast-starting Magic to 128-116 win over Pacers

headlines.description: — Darius Garland scored 26 points and undrafted rookie Craig Porter Jr. had a career-high 21 points, powering the Cleveland Cavaliers to a 121-109 victory over the defending NBA champion Denver Nuggets on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Darius Garland scores 26 points as the Cavaliers beat the defending champion Nuggets 121-109

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis had 32 points and 13 rebounds, De'Aaron Fox scored 30 and the Sacramento Kings beat the Dallas Mavericks 129-113 on Sunday night for their sixth consecutive victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis, Fox lead Kings past Mavs 129-113 for 6th consecutive win

headlines.description: — Kristaps Porzingis scored 26 points, including the winning dunk with 1:01 left, as the the Boston Celtics held on for a 102-100 victory over the Memphis Grizzlies on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kristaps Porzingis scores 26, including winning dunk with a minute left as Celtics defeat Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant totaled 39 points, 10 assists and eight rebounds to lead the Suns to a 140-137 double overtime win over the Utah Jazz on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kevin Durant's 39 points leads Suns past Jazz 140-137 in double overtime

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander had 28 points before heading to the bench in the third quarter and the Oklahoma City Thunder won their fifth straight game with a 134-91 rout of the Portland Trail Blazers on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander has 28 points and OKC Thunder routs Blazers 134-91 for 5th straight win

events.name: Houston Rockets at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Going into Sunday night's game, LeBron James wasn't motivated alone by Dillon Brooks' slights against him.
headlines.shortLinkText: James scores season-high 37, hits go-ahead free throw as Lakers hold off Rockets 105-104
